extit_module_t *
extit_module_bind(extit_container_t * container, const void * descriptor, unsigned int flags)
Create a module from a plugin module descriptor. This should be released with extit_module_release().
Parameters:
container - The container interface.
descriptor - The descriptor address.
flags - The module flags (EXTIT_FLAG_*).
Returns:
A module pointer, or NULL if the bind failed.
Since:
1.0

Returns:
A plugin pointer, or NULL if the create failed.

Release a plugin module. This fail if plugins instances still exist for the module.
Parameters:
module - The plugin module.
Returns:
The operation status (EXTIT_STATUS_*).
Since:
1.0
extit_status_t
extit_module_scan(extit_container_t * container, const char * directory, extit_module_scan_callback_t callback, const void * client_data, extit_module_scan_fnfilter_t fnfilter, unsigned int flags)
Scan a directory for plugin modules. fnfilter will be called for each normal file, which should return EXTIT_TRUE, if the filename is acceptable, or EXTIT_FALSE otherwise. For each valid module found and loaded, callback will be called with it. Any module loaded by this function must be released with extit_module_release() to prevent memory and/or resource leaks, even if the callback does not use the module.
Parameters:
container - The container interface.
directory - The directory to scan.
callback - The callback function.
client_data - Additional data to pass to the callback.
fnfilter - The filename filter callback function.
flags - The module flags (EXTIT_FLAG_*).
Returns:
The operation status (EXTIT_STATUS_*).
Since:
1.0
extit_status_t
extit_module_scan_wc(extit_container_t * container, const wchar_t * directory, extit_module_scan_callback_t callback, const void * client_data, extit_module_scan_fnfilter_wc_t fnfilter, unsigned int flags)
Scan a directory for plugin modules. fnfilter will be called for each normal file, which should return EXTIT_TRUE, if the filename is acceptable, or EXTIT_FALSE otherwise. For each valid module found and loaded, callback will be called with it. Any module loaded by this function must be released with extit_module_release() to prevent memory and/or resource leaks, even if the callback does not use the module. This function is only available on platforms that support wide character filenames.
Parameters:
container - The container interface.
directory - The directory to scan.
callback - The callback function.
client_data - Additional data to pass to the callback.
fnfilter - The filename filter callback function.
flags - The module flags (EXTIT_FLAG_*).
Returns:
The operation status (EXTIT_STATUS_*).
Since:
1.0
extit_bool_t
extit_module_scan_fnfilter_default(const char * libname, size_t length)
A standard filename filter. Checks are case-insensitive on Windows and macOS and case-sensitive for other platforms.
Parameters:
libname - The name of the library file.
length - The length of the library filename.
Returns:
EXTIT_TRUE to accept the file, or EXTIT_FALSE to reject it.
Since:
1.0
extit_bool_t
extit_module_scan_fnfilter_wc_default(const wchar_t * libname, size_t length)
A standard filename filter. Checks are case-insensitive on Windows and macOS and case-sensitive for other platforms. This function is only available on platforms that support wide character filenames.
Parameters:
libname - The name of the library file.
length - The length of the library filename (in characters).
Returns:
EXTIT_TRUE to accept the file, or EXTIT_FALSE to reject it.
Since:
1.0
